records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which amends the charge to child enticement, contrary to Section 948.07(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
GUILTY Plea entered to the amended charge.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for seven (7) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Comply with sex offender treatment;
3) Register with and comply with the Sex Offender Registry for fifteen (15) years after the period of probation is completed;
4) No contact with children unless approved by the agent;
5) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination at the agents discretion;
6) No possession or use of internet enabled devices without agents approval;
7) Provide DNA sample;
8) Spend sixty (60) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 03-22-16 by 6:00 p.m.;
9) Pay court costs;
10) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
